        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 8:20PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 820 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gail, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gail.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
